Please note that this script assumes that the user provides a valid function in terms of x and two valid numbers for a and b. If the input is not correct, the script will display an error message and exit.

Also, this script uses `eval` to evaluate the user-provided function. This may be a security concern as it allows the user to execute arbitrary code. If you want to prevent this, you can replace the `derivative` function with a custom implementation that supports specific functions (e.g., polynomials).

